  "prompt": "How much bands needs to get admission in UC berkeley for indian student after 12th?",
  "response": "UC Berkeley doesn't use a \"bands\" system for admissions. They use a holistic review process, considering many factors. Also, admission is directly based on high school performance after 12th grade. You apply *after* you complete 12th grade (or equivalent).\n\nHowever, if you meant what score in the 12th board exams are necessary to get admission into UC Berkeley as an Indian student, here is the information:\n\n*   **Academic Excellence:** UC Berkeley is highly competitive. You'll need exceptional grades. Generally, aim for **above 95% overall** in your 12th-grade board exams (CBSE, ISC, or state boards). Some successful applicants have near-perfect scores.\n*   **Competitive Subjects:** Focus on achieving top marks in subjects relevant to your intended major. For example, if you want to study engineering, excel in math, physics, and chemistry.\n*   **Holistic Review:** Grades are just one part. UC Berkeley looks for:\n    *   **Extracurricular Activities:** Meaningful involvement in clubs, sports, volunteer work, research, or personal projects.  Leadership roles are a plus.\n    *   **Essays:** Well-written essays that showcase your personality, experiences, and goals. They want to see your critical thinking and communication skills.\n    *   **Letters of Recommendation:** Strong letters from teachers or mentors who can speak to your abilities and potential.\n    *   **Standardized Tests:** UC Berkeley is test-blind, meaning they do not consider SAT or ACT scores in their admission process.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\n*   **Grades:** Aim for above 95% in your 12th-grade board exams.\n*   **Beyond Grades:** Exceptional extracurriculars, strong essays, and compelling letters of recommendation are crucial.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Competition:** Admission is highly competitive, so even with excellent grades, admission isn't guaranteed.\n*   **Major-Specific Requirements:** Some majors may have specific course prerequisites. Research the requirements for your chosen field of study.\n*   **Financial Aid:** UC Berkeley offers financial aid to international students, but it's highly competitive. Explore financial aid options and requirements early in the application process.\n\nI strongly suggest visiting the UC Berkeley admissions website for international students for the most up-to-date information and application requirements.",
